    "1": {
      "text": "According to Hegel, activities are not valuable in terms of their efficacy in realizing ends. Rather, their value is  that  they  are  both  constitutive  and  formative  of our personalities. They transform our identities and, consequently, our self-conception.",
      "label": "claim"
    },
    "2": {
      "text": "I have come to think of the activity of knitting, if properly undertaken, as neither mindless nor archaic but can be, to return to the Hegelian discussion introduced above, formative of our personality and the knitwear produced a material embodiment of our freedom.",
      "label": "claim"
    },
    "3": {
      "text": "If knitting can only be justified in terms of the outcomes produced, then most knitting is not justifiable.",
      "label": "claim"
    },
